{"TopicId":131371,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"The Void UPDATE I\u0026#039;m done with this 1/4/17","CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-04T17:36:44Z","PageNum":3,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-21T09:00:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222421930\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456030842\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022fredinno\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, fredinno said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n35 C colder than Earth is -19 C.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barnard%27s_Star\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barnard%27s_Star\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBarnard\u0027s Star has only 30% of the Sun\u0027s Mettalicity, so any planets would be small, and would be more concentrated in things like water.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know, that\u0027s the temperature of planet c.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also know that, that\u0027s why I added only 2 planets, one covered in water, and roughly the size of Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T14:30:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBump.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease help \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T14:38:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith what, exactly? \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152800-spaceception/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152800\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152800-spaceception/\u0022\u003E@Spaceception\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T14:41:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/127797-bill-phil/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022127797\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/127797-bill-phil/\u0022\u003E@Bill Phil\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe amount of bombs I\u0027ll need to get to 8% the Speed of light (And slow down), here are the Spacecraft\u0027s specs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe spacecraft is 1.2 km long,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Bomb container is a cylinder 250 meters long,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe bombs are about 15 centimeters long, and weigh 140 kg (Like the original design during Project Orion),\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe sail is 350 meters wide and about 60 meters deep.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-28T14:46:06Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2016 02:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T15:02:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433470\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456670471\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/127797-bill-phil/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022127797\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/127797-bill-phil/\u0022\u003E@Bill Phil\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe amount of bombs I\u0027ll need to get to 8% the Speed of light (And slow down), here are the Spacecraft\u0027s specs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe spacecraft is 1.2 km long,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Bomb container is a cylinder 250 meters long,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe bombs are about 15 centimeters long, and weigh 140 kg (Like the original design during Project Orion),\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe sail is 350 meters wide and about 60 meters deep.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need the ISP and the total mass, which will give us the total mass of bombs needed and thus the total number of bombs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T15:21:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433490\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456671759\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need the ISP and the total mass, which will give us the total mass of bombs needed and thus the total number of bombs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of the better variants of Orion had an ISP of ~13,000 seconds, so looking at the Medusa (Which is more efficient), I\u0027d say between 33,000 seconds\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDry mass: 10,000 tonnes, Wet mass (bombs): 20,500 tonnes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-28T15:24:15Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2016 03:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T15:52:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433529\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456672905\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of the better variants of Orion had an ISP of ~13,000 seconds, so looking at the Medusa (Which is more efficient), I\u0027d say between 33,000 seconds\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDry mass: 10,000 tonnes, Wet mass (bombs): 20,500 tonnes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMedusa is only more efficient due to mass savings, really.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n.08c cruise, and braking?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n.16c total Dv\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me run up the numbers...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry to say, but you\u0027re mass ratio is looking like 2.88 times 10 raised to the 64th.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAccording to your numbers you only have a few hundred kps. You\u0027re gonna need better engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, if you know your mass values, you already have your answers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T15:57:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433565\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456674766\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, if you know your mass values, you already have your answers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah... I was a stupid there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433565\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456674766\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry to say, but you\u0027re mass ratio is looking like 2.88 times 10 raised to the 64th.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAccording to your numbers you only have a few hundred kps. You\u0027re gonna need better engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so less mass or more mass?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:17:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433571\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456675028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah... I was a stupid there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so less mass or more mass?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeither. More ISP or less speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet\u0027s say your mass ratio is exactly \u0022e\u0022. The Ln of e is 1. That means that you need an exhaust velocity of .16c to get .16c of DeltaV. Now, in space, ratios like 10, 15, or 20 are more possible, and it really depends on a bunch of factors. But your ship doesn\u0027t need to survive 1g, so a lot more is possible. Maybe inflatable Graphene\u00A0tanks? Idk.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-28T16:17:58Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2016 04:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bill Phil\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:21:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433602\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456676265\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeither. More ISP or less speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright, new ISP 45,000 seconds\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nspeed 11% light speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:31:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456676473\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright, new ISP 45,000 seconds\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nspeed 11% light speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat won\u0027t change much. You need ISPs thousands of times of that to not have enormous masses. I mean masses larger than Jupiter, here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:33:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456677107\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat won\u0027t change much. You need ISPs thousands of times of that to not have enormous masses. I mean masses larger than Jupiter, here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, well than what would be your ISP/Bomb mass/Speed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:35:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456677188\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, well than what would be your ISP/Bomb mass/Speed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need at least .001c ISP to get a DV of 1% light speed with a mass ratio of e. Preferably faster.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMedusa may not even work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI messed up with my analogy. It\u0027s galactic masses, not jupiter masses. And if not that, solar masses.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-28T16:37:49Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2016 04:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bill Phil\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:37:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456677306\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need at least .001c ISP to get a DV of 1% light speed with a mass ratio of e. Preferably faster.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMedusa may not even work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI messed up with my analogy. It\u0027s galactic masses, not jupiter masses.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait, GALACTIC masses!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo how was the original Orion (On paper) able to get to 10% ls if it requires so much mass?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:39:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456677467\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait, GALACTIC masses!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo how was the original Orion (On paper) able to get to 10% ls if it requires so much mass?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey had high ISPs, like, millions of seconds. Orion gets better as it gets bigger.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey also had 8 million tons of total (wet) mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-28T16:39:53Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2016 04:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bill Phil\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:50:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456677543\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey had high ISPs, like, millions of seconds. Orion gets better as it gets bigger.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo if I increase the size of the spacecraft to 150,000 tonnes, and do a mild switch to Orion, with a ISP of 250,000, would 6% ls be doable?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:53:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456678237\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo if I increase the size of the spacecraft to 150,000 tonnes, and do a mild switch to Orion, with a ISP of 250,000, would 6% ls be doable?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet\u0027s be really nice: you get to use a mag\u00A0sail to brake. Only need 6% DV.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re mass ratio is in the thousands. Maybe multiple stages?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith\u00A0three stages, each one with 2%c deltaV, you can have a lower double digit\u00A0mass ratio.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-28T16:55:53Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2016 04:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bill Phil\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:56:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456678418\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet\u0027s be really nice: you get to use a mag\u00A0sail to brake. Only need 6% DV.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re mass ratio is in the thousands. Maybe multiple stages?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse asparagus staging to release empty mass? Both Bombs and resources?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:57:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould do this even easier with laser sails, braking with mag sails.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456678606\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse asparagus staging to release empty mass? Both Bombs and resources?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook at the Daedalus/Icarus designs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T17:00:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433653\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456678621\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould do this even easier with laser sails, braking with mag sails.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need to build the lasers first, and this is in the middle of the end of world, where we have 15 years to build the spacecraft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T17:05:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456678804\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need to build the lasers first, and this is in the middle of the end of world, where we have 15 years to build the spacecraft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEasy:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunch a fleet of Orions to build the lasers in low solar orbit. Could probably get there in a month or two, bring an asteroid and make some lasers. Build the laser sail and bam! You have a laser starship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s happening to Earth?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T17:08:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456679117\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEasy:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunch a fleet of Orions to build the lasers in low solar orbit. Could probably get there in a month or two, bring an asteroid and make some lasers. Build the laser sail and bam! You have a laser starship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s happening to Earth?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would work, but how big/heavy will the sail be? I heard that in order to get to 8% ls, you need a sail the size of Texas (Alright, not that big, maybe 1/3 the size).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA Black Hole is gonna wreck some $#!t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd the plot is gonna be big, at least near the end \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T17:13:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433663\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456679317\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would work, but how big/heavy will the sail be? I heard that in order to get to 8% ls, you need a sail the size of Texas (Alright, not that big, maybe 1/3 the size).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA Black Hole is gonna wreck some $#!t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd the plot is gonna be big, at least near the end \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you may not even need to go to another star system. Orbital colonies seem much more doable, unless the whole solar system is exploding. And you could just build a bunch and go a bunch of AU out...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe speed of the sail depends on size and power of the laser.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-28T17:15:47Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2016 05:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bill Phil\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T17:15:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456679624\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you may not even need to go to another star system. Orbital colonies seem much more doable, unless the whole solar system is exploding.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, it\u0027s a Black hole entering inside the orbit of Jupiter, It\u0027ll either fall into the Sun, the Black hole, or become rogue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T17:21:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433653\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456678621\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook at the Daedalus/Icarus designs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s too theoretical, even today, I need something near-term, like NPP, or maybe laser sails.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}